{"image_id": "HAL_2016_page_68", "image_size": [1257, 1632], "ocr": [{"text": "Our total outstanding net trade receivables in Venezuela were $610 million as of December 31, 2016, excluding the", "bbox": [169.0, 81.9, 1135.0, 105.4]}, {"text": "promissory note receivable discussed above, compared to $704 million as of December 31, 2015, which represents 15% and", "bbox": [93.9, 107.0, 1135.5, 130.4]}, {"text": "14% of total company trade receivables for the respective periods. The majority of our Venezuela receivables are United States", "bbox": [93.9, 132.0, 1156.9, 155.4]}, {"text": "dollar-denominated receivables. Of the $610 million receivables in Venezuela as of December 31, 2016, $409 million has been", "bbox": [93.9, 157.0, 1157.0, 180.4]}, {"text": "classified as long-term and included within “Other assets” on our consolidated balance sheets.", "bbox": [93.9, 182.0, 888.6, 205.4]}, {"text": "As a result of market conditions in Venezuela and the continued delays in collecting payments on our receivables in", "bbox": [168.9, 232.0, 1138.0, 255.5]}, {"text": "the country, we began curtailing activity in Venezuela during the first quarter of 2016. See Note 14 and “Management’s", "bbox": [93.9, 257.1, 1094.0, 280.5]}, {"text": "Discussion and Analysis of Financial Condition and Results of Operations – Business Environment and Results of Operations”", "bbox": [93.9, 282.1, 1157.2, 305.5]}, {"text": "for additional information about the promissory note exchange.", "bbox": [93.9, 307.1, 626.9, 330.5]}, {"text": "The following table presents a rollforward of our allowance for bad debts for 2014, 2015 and 2016.", "bbox": [169.0, 357.1, 1007.4, 380.5]}, {"text": "Millions of dollars", "bbox": [176.2, 440.6, 336.5, 463.8]}, {"text": "Balance at", "bbox": [605.5, 398.8, 698.0, 422.3]}, {"text": "Beginning of", "bbox": [594.7, 419.6, 709.0, 443.0]}, {"text": "Period", "bbox": [622.0, 440.4, 681.7, 463.8]}, {"text": "Charged to", "bbox": [728.6, 398.8, 825.3, 422.3]}, {"tex